<p><code>Request object</code> and <code>response object</code> are not available in <code>ajax</code> call. And Gmail and many other sites use Ajax and authentication and authorization. </p>  <p>My question is: how they authenticate?</p>  <p>since authentication information mostly stored in <code>Session</code> object` and Session object is not available in ajax call.</p>  <p>I am from <code>asp.net</code> background.</p>